\subsection{Modelling response times}
\newtext{While we do not have the same amount of control in an AMT study that we would have an a lab setting, we can measure the time between presenting a lineup and the time that a participant submits the results on it. A histogram of these times is given in Figure~\ref{fig:histogram}. Response times are extremely skew. In the model we therefore use the log of response times $T = \left(t_{ijk}\right)_{n \times 1}$:}
